subsection.p:
Function notation is a way to tell the reader information about the input and how to use it to generate an output. Again, the way it works is:
f(\text{input})=\text{output}
Whatever is in the parenthesis is the input.

Or, you can put something complicated like \frac{x^2}{x^2 + 1} into the formula,
which would look like this:

  f\mathopen{}\left(\frac{x^2}{x^2 + 1}\right)\mathclose{} = \mathopen{}\left(\frac{x^2}{x^2 + 1}\right)^2\mathclose{} - \mathopen{}\left(\frac{x^2}{x^2 + 1}\right)\mathclose{}

